A modified radial diffusion assay92–94 was used to test antimicrobial activity of protein extracts. E. coli TOP 10 cells were inoculated overnight at 37 °C in liquid casein peptone soybean flour peptone (CASO) medium. 10 µL samples of the overnight cultures were inoculated in 10 mL CASO, and grown for 3 h. The cultures were then pelleted by centrifugation (3000 x g, 10 min, 20 °C) and the pellets were rinsed carefully with cold (4 °C) 10 mM sodium phosphate buffer, pH 7.4 (NAPB), followed by resuspension in 5 mL NAPB. The OD620 was measured in the suspension and a 10x diluted suspension, and the number of colony-forming units (CFU) was determined by the following equation 1.1CFU/mL=OD620×2.5×108\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
